President Donald Trump delivered a speech at the National Rifle Association (NRA) Annual Meeting in Indianapolis, Indiana. He thanked the NRA and its members for their support and emphasized his commitment to defending the Second Amendment. Trump highlighted the importance of protecting American rights and freedoms, including the right to bear arms. He also discussed his administration's efforts to reduce violent crime and improve school safety. Trump praised the bravery of individuals who used guns to defend themselves and others in dangerous situations. He announced that the United States would revoke its signature from the United Nations Arms Trade Treaty and called on NRA members to support him in the upcoming elections.